radiographic_examinations.findings: A blind-ending fluid filled tubular structure seen in the right lower quadrant with hyperemia, and surrounding edema. There is a shadowing appendicolith seen in its mid portion. The structure is dilated measuring 9-10 mm in the short axis and is non-compressible. The uterus is normal in size. The endometrium is homogenous, measuring 4 mm. The ovaries are normal. There is minimal free fluid seen in the pelvis.
